1
00:00:10,063 --> 00:00:12,438
-[groans]
-[guard] Come on!

2
00:00:14,729 --> 00:00:16,854
[Dr. Merati]
"They that love beyond the world

3
00:00:16,938 --> 00:00:18,229
cannot be separated by it.

4
00:00:18,563 --> 00:00:20,604
Death cannot kill what never dies."

5
00:00:20,938 --> 00:00:23,813
[Governor] With Vanessa, at least
I had a sense someone had his ear,

6
00:00:23,896 --> 00:00:25,438
someone could rein him in.

7
00:00:25,521 --> 00:00:27,938
Pressure on my office is immense.
I'm getting it from all sides.

8
00:00:28,021 --> 00:00:31,771
Hi, Marge. I am here to solve
your City Hall problem.

9
00:00:32,229 --> 00:00:34,188
[Buck] We work for a man
who can change your life.

10
00:00:34,271 --> 00:00:37,479
All he asks in return is loyalty.
Make a choice.

11
00:00:37,979 --> 00:00:39,563
-What is this?
-Daniel, please.

12
00:00:39,646 --> 00:00:41,438
I don't even know
if I can protect you anymore.

13
00:00:41,521 --> 00:00:42,646
Protect me from what?

14
00:00:42,729 --> 00:00:44,438
-[cell phone buzzes]
-From him.

15
00:00:46,229 --> 00:00:49,354
[Fisk] We have reason to believe
that Matt Murdock survived the attack.

16
00:00:49,438 --> 00:00:51,438
Help find the lawyer from Hell's Kitchen.

17
00:00:51,521 --> 00:00:53,688
Let's bring this hero home.

18
00:00:53,771 --> 00:00:54,813
Thank you.

19
00:00:55,688 --> 00:00:57,854
-[groans]
-I can't let you do it, Karen.

20
00:00:57,938 --> 00:01:01,396
[Karen] What if this doesn't end
until one of you goes down?

21
00:01:01,479 --> 00:01:03,354
Push those motherfuckers back!

22
00:01:05,479 --> 00:01:06,646
Holy shit.

23
00:01:06,729 --> 00:01:08,896
Karen fuckin' Page.

24
00:01:18,229 --> 00:01:21,938
[sirens wailing in distance]

25
00:01:25,604 --> 00:01:26,604
[man] One avocado.

26
00:01:29,188 --> 00:01:31,229
[reporter 1] According to
city officials, vigilantes...

27
00:01:31,313 --> 00:01:32,604
[reporter 2]
...riots at City Hall...

28
00:01:32,688 --> 00:01:35,729
[reporter 3] Last night's attack
on City Hall by criminals...

29
00:01:36,563 --> 00:01:39,563
-[man yells indistinctly]
-[sirens wail, helicopter hovers]

30
00:01:39,646 --> 00:01:42,188
-[reporter 4] Protesters...
-[reporter 5] ...attacked by Task Force.

31
00:01:44,896 --> 00:01:46,938
-Three injured.
-[reporter 4] Two dead.

32
00:01:48,354 --> 00:01:51,854
[reporter 6] Mayor Fisk vows
to restore order to this city.

33
00:01:53,063 --> 00:01:56,396
[♪ psychedelic rock music playing,
David Bowie "It Ain't Easy"]

34
00:01:56,479 --> 00:02:00,354
♪ When you climb
to the top of the mountain ♪

35
00:02:00,479 --> 00:02:03,688
♪ Look out over the sea ♪

36
00:02:04,479 --> 00:02:10,646
♪ Think about the places, perhaps
where a young man could be ♪

37
00:02:10,729 --> 00:02:15,188
♪ Then you jump back down
to the rooftops ♪

38
00:02:15,271 --> 00:02:18,396
♪ Look out over the town ♪

39
00:02:18,479 --> 00:02:22,063
♪ Think about all of the strange things ♪

40
00:02:22,146 --> 00:02:24,313
♪ Circulating 'round ♪

41
00:02:24,396 --> 00:02:27,813
♪ It ain't easy ♪

42
00:02:27,896 --> 00:02:30,313
♪ It ain't easy ♪

43
00:02:31,354 --> 00:02:36,563
♪ It ain't easy to get to heaven
when you're goin' down ♪

44
00:02:38,854 --> 00:02:43,521
♪ Well, all the people
have got their problems ♪

45
00:02:43,604 --> 00:02:45,729
♪ That ain't nothin' new ♪

46
00:02:47,146 --> 00:02:50,771
♪ With the help of the good Lord ♪

47
00:02:50,854 --> 00:02:53,438
♪ We can all pull on through ♪

48
00:02:53,521 --> 00:02:55,896
♪ We can all pull on through ♪

49
00:02:55,979 --> 00:02:57,521
[inmates chattering indistinctly]

50
00:02:57,604 --> 00:03:00,979
♪ And get there in the end ♪

51
00:03:01,063 --> 00:03:04,396
♪ Sometimes it'll take you right up ♪

52
00:03:04,479 --> 00:03:07,104
♪ And sometimes down again ♪

53
00:03:07,188 --> 00:03:10,688
♪ It ain't easy ♪

54
00:03:10,771 --> 00:03:14,063
♪ It ain't easy ♪

55
00:03:14,146 --> 00:03:19,188
♪ It ain't easy to get to heaven
when you're goin' down ♪

56
00:03:19,271 --> 00:03:23,729
-[door buzzes open, closes]
-♪ It ain't easy ♪

57
00:03:23,813 --> 00:03:25,979
[woman] I don't know.
Come on, everybody.

58
00:03:26,063 --> 00:03:27,646
Hey, where are my cigarettes?

59
00:03:27,729 --> 00:03:32,479
♪ It ain't easy to get to heaven
when you're goin' down ♪

60
00:03:52,188 --> 00:03:53,646
[Fisk] Hello, Miss Page.

61
00:03:55,896 --> 00:03:58,813
You have... taken people from me.

62
00:04:01,479 --> 00:04:03,771
And out there, they believe that you're...

63
00:04:04,229 --> 00:04:05,563
a hero.

64
00:04:06,438 --> 00:04:08,146
Yet I believe in order.

65
00:04:09,854 --> 00:04:11,146
And you are a criminal.

66
00:04:11,896 --> 00:04:12,896
Worse,

67
00:04:13,188 --> 00:04:15,896
you're the sidekick
of a deranged vigilante.

68
00:04:17,771 --> 00:04:18,771
You,

69
00:04:19,063 --> 00:04:21,021
broken and deluded,

70
00:04:21,688 --> 00:04:23,521
you abet his crimes.

71
00:04:24,188 --> 00:04:25,188
For what?

72
00:04:26,104 --> 00:04:27,229
Love?

73
00:04:28,479 --> 00:04:29,813
Ha!

74
00:04:48,021 --> 00:04:50,188
You know,
I've never seen you scared before.

75
00:04:52,313 --> 00:04:53,521
I kinda like it.

76
00:04:54,604 --> 00:04:56,813
No, not fear.

77
00:04:56,896 --> 00:04:58,688
[gasps, winces]

78
00:04:59,188 --> 00:05:00,521
-[choking]
-Order,

79
00:05:00,604 --> 00:05:01,604
Miss Page.

80
00:05:02,313 --> 00:05:03,313
Order.

81
00:05:03,563 --> 00:05:04,813
No, no.

82
00:05:04,896 --> 00:05:07,563
No, you took it too far last night,
and you know it.

83
00:05:07,646 --> 00:05:09,521
And the city knows it!

84
00:05:09,604 --> 00:05:11,896
[choking]

85
00:05:12,854 --> 00:05:15,771
[gasps and coughs]

86
00:05:16,729 --> 00:05:18,563
You have one phone call.

87
00:05:19,938 --> 00:05:21,354
Choose it wisely.

88
00:05:21,438 --> 00:05:23,729
[pants, chuckles softly]

89
00:05:29,271 --> 00:05:32,563
[♪ theme music playing]

90
00:07:10,813 --> 00:07:13,354
[snoring]

91
00:07:15,188 --> 00:07:17,396
-[gasps]
-Good morning, sunshine.

92
00:07:17,479 --> 00:07:18,729
Jessica.

93
00:07:18,813 --> 00:07:20,271
Wait. Hold, hold, hold on.

94
00:07:20,354 --> 00:07:22,021
Listen, before you choose violence--

95
00:07:22,104 --> 00:07:23,979
You sent your assholes to my house.

96
00:07:24,063 --> 00:07:26,479
That was a mistake. They were
just supposed to tell you to back off.

97
00:07:26,563 --> 00:07:27,813
With my daughter there.

98
00:07:27,896 --> 00:07:30,104
I would never hurt your kid--
I love children.

99
00:07:30,188 --> 00:07:31,313
You listen to me.

100
00:07:31,396 --> 00:07:34,563
If you ever come at me
or Danielle ever again,

101
00:07:34,646 --> 00:07:36,396
-I swear to God, I will kill you.
-[groans]

102
00:07:36,896 --> 00:07:38,354
-Do you understand me?
-Yeah.

103
00:07:38,438 --> 00:07:39,521
Please don't kill me.

104
00:07:40,479 --> 00:07:42,896
Also, I'm not really sure you can anymore,

105
00:07:42,979 --> 00:07:46,104
'cause a little birdie said your powers
ain't what they used to be.

106
00:07:49,479 --> 00:07:51,271
Speaking of little birdies,

107
00:07:51,938 --> 00:07:53,188
you're talkin' a lotta shit

108
00:07:53,271 --> 00:07:56,271
for a guy sittin' there in his underwear
with very limited options.

109
00:07:56,354 --> 00:07:59,771
Don't forget, I am the only one
that can connect you

110
00:08:00,188 --> 00:08:01,188
with Luke.

111
00:08:05,813 --> 00:08:06,979
Where is he?

112
00:08:07,063 --> 00:08:09,271
He is overseas.
He's doin' the Lord's work,

113
00:08:09,354 --> 00:08:10,354
so you don't have to.

114
00:08:10,813 --> 00:08:14,229
-You're behind Fisk's arms deal.
-No, I'm not.

115
00:08:14,313 --> 00:08:16,938
Because a couple
anti-social vigilantes blew 'em up.

116
00:08:17,021 --> 00:08:18,938
No arms, no deal. [scoffs]

117
00:08:19,021 --> 00:08:21,521
-Thanks for that, by the way.
-Why are you covering for him?

118
00:08:21,604 --> 00:08:22,688
I'm not, not anymore.

119
00:08:23,229 --> 00:08:24,521
It's actually the opposite.

120
00:08:26,229 --> 00:08:27,813
The Governor wants Fisk...

121
00:08:28,438 --> 00:08:30,104
-out.
-Good, that's...

122
00:08:30,188 --> 00:08:31,229
That's great news.

123
00:08:31,313 --> 00:08:34,229
Yeah, except he just went apeshit
on his own voters.

124
00:08:34,313 --> 00:08:35,729
I don't think she can do it.

125
00:08:36,438 --> 00:08:39,354
The way I see it,
this goes all kinds of wrong

126
00:08:39,688 --> 00:08:41,271
for Governor McCaffrey.

127
00:08:42,979 --> 00:08:46,854
[scoffs] Oh, Christ.

128
00:08:47,979 --> 00:08:49,646
[Matt] Fisk is gonna kill the Governor?

129
00:08:50,104 --> 00:08:51,771
[Jess] That's what Charles suggested.

130
00:08:52,063 --> 00:08:53,313
Very strongly.

131
00:08:53,396 --> 00:08:54,396
And you believe him?

132
00:08:55,021 --> 00:08:57,521
This guy was working with Fisk
until about a minute ago.

133
00:08:58,188 --> 00:09:01,021
I don't believe a word that asshole says,
but in this case...

134
00:09:01,104 --> 00:09:02,771
-Yeah.
-...it does track.

135
00:09:03,854 --> 00:09:07,604
[sighs] She's the only one
who can revoke the Freeport's charter.

136
00:09:08,729 --> 00:09:11,729
If Fisk puts one of his puppets
in the Governor's office,

137
00:09:12,729 --> 00:09:13,729
New York is his.

138
00:09:14,313 --> 00:09:16,354
And we are on another rooftop.

139
00:09:16,688 --> 00:09:19,438
Yeah, I'm meeting a friend.
Cherry, Jessica. Jessica, Cherry.

140
00:09:19,521 --> 00:09:21,229
Hey, big fan of your work.

141
00:09:21,771 --> 00:09:22,771
Go on.

142
00:09:23,229 --> 00:09:24,229
And?

143
00:09:25,396 --> 00:09:27,646
-Karen's at the 15th Precinct.
-Nice, thank you, Cherry.

144
00:09:27,729 --> 00:09:29,313
All right, now, hold on there, cowboy.

145
00:09:29,396 --> 00:09:30,813
They booked her legit.

146
00:09:30,896 --> 00:09:33,063
Prints, photo, phone call, the works.

147
00:09:33,563 --> 00:09:35,563
They're fast-trackin' her
to Vigilante Court.

148
00:09:35,646 --> 00:09:38,563
You go in there and bust her out,
you are the criminal he says you are.

149
00:09:38,646 --> 00:09:39,896
She's not safe there.

150
00:09:39,979 --> 00:09:42,188
If he was gonna hurt her,
he'd have done it already.

151
00:09:42,271 --> 00:09:45,771
Look, I'm told he went to the precinct,
they talked, he left.

152
00:09:47,146 --> 00:09:48,188
Fisk?

153
00:09:48,729 --> 00:09:49,896
Son of a bitch.

154
00:09:51,313 --> 00:09:52,438
He's making it legal.

155
00:09:54,146 --> 00:09:55,563
We have anybody at the 15th?

156
00:09:55,646 --> 00:09:57,813
We do. Come on, Matt, I'm all over this.

157
00:09:59,979 --> 00:10:02,104
And you? You stickin' around?

158
00:10:04,229 --> 00:10:05,646
I haven't decided yet.

159
00:10:05,729 --> 00:10:06,813
City needs you.

160
00:10:06,896 --> 00:10:09,063
Tsk. I've heard that before.

161
00:10:09,146 --> 00:10:10,563
[chuckles] Me, too.

162
00:10:11,313 --> 00:10:12,979
-Nice to meet you, Cherry.
-You, too.

163
00:10:13,604 --> 00:10:14,604
Matt.

164
00:10:16,063 --> 00:10:18,063
So, what do ya think?
Are you gonna hit the 15th?

165
00:10:18,146 --> 00:10:20,021
I don't know. There might be another way.

166
00:10:20,104 --> 00:10:21,604
-We--
-I can't help you there.

167
00:10:22,188 --> 00:10:23,896
I did what I came here to do.

168
00:10:23,979 --> 00:10:25,646
I got Charles off my ass.

169
00:10:26,896 --> 00:10:28,563
I need to get home. I have Danielle.

170
00:10:28,646 --> 00:10:31,354
I know, you don't need to explain.
I understand.

171
00:10:31,438 --> 00:10:32,854
Fisk isn't gonna stop.

172
00:10:34,521 --> 00:10:36,188
Unless someone puts him down.

173
00:10:36,521 --> 00:10:38,146
Forgotten how encouraging you were.

174
00:10:39,521 --> 00:10:40,729
Don't get yourself killed.

175
00:10:43,104 --> 00:10:44,271
The city needs you.

176
00:10:57,104 --> 00:10:58,896
[bones cracking]

177
00:11:15,229 --> 00:11:16,229
So...

178
00:11:18,021 --> 00:11:19,021
what now?

179
00:11:20,438 --> 00:11:21,896
You wanted one good deed, right?

180
00:11:23,146 --> 00:11:24,688
So we could balance the scales?

181
00:11:25,188 --> 00:11:26,229
-Yeah.
-All right.

182
00:11:26,313 --> 00:11:27,896
-Sure.
-I got it for you.

183
00:11:30,229 --> 00:11:31,604
But first, know this.

184
00:11:34,188 --> 00:11:35,646
I hate you for Foggy.

185
00:11:38,146 --> 00:11:39,521
I hate you for Father Lantom,

186
00:11:39,604 --> 00:11:40,854
for Agent Nadeem.

187
00:11:42,646 --> 00:11:46,104
And every life you've wasted for no reason
other than your own twisted soul.

188
00:11:48,479 --> 00:11:49,938
Part of me wants to kill you.

189
00:11:52,646 --> 00:11:53,646
And...

190
00:11:55,438 --> 00:11:57,104
part of me needs to forgive you.

191
00:11:58,479 --> 00:11:59,479
Yeah.

192
00:12:01,729 --> 00:12:03,396
Well... [clears throat]

193
00:12:06,271 --> 00:12:07,271
Thanks.

194
00:12:07,979 --> 00:12:08,979
Don't do that.

195
00:12:09,063 --> 00:12:10,813
It's not for you, it's for them.

196
00:12:11,813 --> 00:12:13,146
Now go, disappear,

197
00:12:13,229 --> 00:12:14,438
die, I don't care.

198
00:12:15,896 --> 00:12:17,313
But if you mean what you say,

199
00:12:18,771 --> 00:12:21,063
you wanna do one good thing
in a life full of shit,

200
00:12:21,688 --> 00:12:22,771
I got it for ya.

201
00:12:24,521 --> 00:12:27,104
You know I can't make any promises, right?

202
00:12:31,104 --> 00:12:32,563
Wouldn't believe you if you did.

203
00:12:40,688 --> 00:12:42,271
What do you want me to do?

204
00:12:43,521 --> 00:12:45,688
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

205
00:12:48,938 --> 00:12:50,813
[police sirens wailing]

206
00:12:55,188 --> 00:12:56,771
[footsteps approaching]

207
00:13:06,104 --> 00:13:07,104
Brett.

208
00:13:08,021 --> 00:13:09,771
-Hey.
-Hey, Karen.

209
00:13:11,063 --> 00:13:12,063
It's been a while.

210
00:13:12,146 --> 00:13:13,146
Yeah.

211
00:13:14,021 --> 00:13:16,354
[sighs] Wondered why
they brought me to the 15th.

212
00:13:16,438 --> 00:13:19,104
Hey, you know, Chief of Detective
gets to pull a few strings.

213
00:13:19,188 --> 00:13:21,063
Yeah, yeah. Hotshot, huh?

214
00:13:24,521 --> 00:13:25,521
Fisk was here.

215
00:13:26,854 --> 00:13:27,854
I know.

216
00:13:28,479 --> 00:13:29,771
Only so much I can do.

217
00:13:30,854 --> 00:13:31,854
I know.

218
00:13:36,104 --> 00:13:37,438
-What are you doing?
-[unlocking]

219
00:13:38,438 --> 00:13:39,438
Come with me.

220
00:13:41,104 --> 00:13:42,104
Come.

221
00:13:46,938 --> 00:13:48,104
Let's go.

222
00:13:59,146 --> 00:14:00,688
[Daredevil sighs in relief]

223
00:14:04,854 --> 00:14:06,521
-I'm so sorry.
-I'm sorry.

224
00:14:06,938 --> 00:14:08,896
I'm sorry,
I shouldn't have said what I did.

225
00:14:08,979 --> 00:14:09,979
You know...

226
00:14:11,104 --> 00:14:13,396
we all gotta stop meeting up like this.

227
00:14:14,188 --> 00:14:15,813
I can't cover for that long, but...

228
00:14:16,479 --> 00:14:17,563
you got one minute.

229
00:14:17,646 --> 00:14:18,646
-Okay.
-Thank you.

230
00:14:18,729 --> 00:14:19,854
Listen, we don't
have much time,

231
00:14:19,938 --> 00:14:21,438
-I need--
-I can't go with you.

232
00:14:21,813 --> 00:14:23,688
No, I know. I didn't come to get you.

233
00:14:24,063 --> 00:14:25,479
Fucking great minds, huh?

234
00:14:27,396 --> 00:14:30,563
Look, I don't know what this is, but
it feels like an opportunity. I think...

235
00:14:30,646 --> 00:14:32,729
I have to stay.
I have to face him in court.

236
00:14:36,271 --> 00:14:37,813
They tell you he came to see me?

237
00:14:38,563 --> 00:14:40,688
-You okay?
-[sighs] I'm alive.

238
00:14:41,896 --> 00:14:42,938
He's different.

239
00:14:44,063 --> 00:14:45,521
I don't know
what's going on in his mind,

240
00:14:45,604 --> 00:14:48,229
but he's scheming, and he's planning,
and he's way the hell ahead of us.

241
00:14:48,313 --> 00:14:49,646
I just don't think we can run.

242
00:14:49,729 --> 00:14:50,729
Yeah.

243
00:14:51,313 --> 00:14:53,271
'Cause he's losing the city
and he knows it.

244
00:14:54,354 --> 00:14:57,813
So, he's gonna prosecute you
and humiliate you.

245
00:14:59,063 --> 00:15:00,271
Publicly, legitimately,

246
00:15:00,979 --> 00:15:02,563
and make everyone cheer for it.

247
00:15:06,938 --> 00:15:08,229
Can't say it's not smart.

248
00:15:11,896 --> 00:15:13,813
-That means there'll be cameras.
-Mmm-hmm.

249
00:15:15,146 --> 00:15:16,771
-Exactly.
-Holy shit.

250
00:15:17,938 --> 00:15:18,938
Turns out,

251
00:15:19,354 --> 00:15:21,813
we may have to cross lines
to stop him. Just...

252
00:15:22,646 --> 00:15:23,896
not the ones you think.

253
00:15:25,729 --> 00:15:26,729
Well, then...

254
00:15:33,021 --> 00:15:34,354
No. No.

255
00:15:35,104 --> 00:15:36,104
Matt, you can't.

256
00:15:37,771 --> 00:15:38,896
Yes, I can.

257
00:15:41,479 --> 00:15:43,229
[Brett] All right, time's up.
Let's go.

258
00:15:57,271 --> 00:15:59,438
-I'll be there when you need me.
-[sniffles]

259
00:16:00,146 --> 00:16:01,146
Better be.

260
00:16:17,729 --> 00:16:19,188
[Hochberg] Aiding and abetting murder,

261
00:16:19,271 --> 00:16:22,396
providing material support
to known terrorist, Daredevil.

262
00:16:22,479 --> 00:16:25,396
And that's to say
nothing of inciting a riot.

263
00:16:25,729 --> 00:16:27,771
Just a matter of picking
our strongest charges.

264
00:16:27,854 --> 00:16:29,438
Charge her on all of them.

265
00:16:29,771 --> 00:16:31,104
Convict her on all of them.

266
00:16:32,063 --> 00:16:34,646
-Well, sir, given the time crunch--
-All of them.

267
00:16:36,396 --> 00:16:37,396
Right.

268
00:16:37,938 --> 00:16:38,938
Sir.

269
00:16:39,438 --> 00:16:42,271
Do you know the AG
is gonna want to be involved?

270
00:16:43,813 --> 00:16:45,188
Oh, uh...

271
00:16:46,771 --> 00:16:48,604
Well, what he and Albany wants

272
00:16:48,688 --> 00:16:50,354
is irrelevant at this point.

273
00:16:51,979 --> 00:16:52,979
[knocking on door]

274
00:16:55,771 --> 00:16:58,396
-Dr. Glenn.
-Sir, you asked to see me?

275
00:16:58,479 --> 00:16:59,896
[Fisk] Yes, please come in.

276
00:17:00,396 --> 00:17:02,729
Mr. Hochberg and I,
we were finished, weren't we?

277
00:17:03,438 --> 00:17:05,271
Uh... Of course.

278
00:17:06,813 --> 00:17:07,813
Dr. Glenn,

279
00:17:08,604 --> 00:17:09,938
it's always such a pleasure.

280
00:17:10,021 --> 00:17:11,021
I...

281
00:17:11,104 --> 00:17:14,979
might need a little of your expertise
on this trial, if I may.

282
00:17:15,813 --> 00:17:16,813
Of course.

283
00:17:21,104 --> 00:17:24,271
District Attorney Hochberg is
an interesting fellow, isn't he?

284
00:17:25,896 --> 00:17:28,021
He's a very skilled litigator.

285
00:17:28,104 --> 00:17:29,646
He makes my skin crawl.

286
00:17:30,146 --> 00:17:31,146
[chuckles softly]

287
00:17:31,771 --> 00:17:33,271
Lawyers, you know, they...

288
00:17:34,521 --> 00:17:37,438
use words to twist the truth, don't they?

289
00:17:39,563 --> 00:17:41,188
I think I know what you mean.

290
00:17:41,479 --> 00:17:42,563
I imagine you do.

291
00:17:44,854 --> 00:17:46,313
I wanted to check on you...

292
00:17:47,646 --> 00:17:48,938
person-to-person.

293
00:17:50,646 --> 00:17:51,771
How are you, sir?

294
00:17:53,354 --> 00:17:54,771
I... I don't know.

295
00:17:56,146 --> 00:17:57,771
I haven't been asked that.

296
00:18:06,271 --> 00:18:07,313
I always...

297
00:18:10,146 --> 00:18:12,521
accepted love as a prison.

298
00:18:16,854 --> 00:18:19,396
I just never expected

299
00:18:19,479 --> 00:18:21,313
to be in it alone.

300
00:18:22,438 --> 00:18:24,229
[Heather] Condolences are meaningless.

301
00:18:24,688 --> 00:18:26,396
Thoughts and prayers do nothing.

302
00:18:27,438 --> 00:18:30,021
No one tells you the truth
in times like this,

303
00:18:30,104 --> 00:18:31,104
which is...

304
00:18:32,063 --> 00:18:33,229
This is gonna hurt.

305
00:18:34,813 --> 00:18:35,813
And...

306
00:18:36,396 --> 00:18:37,438
we don't know when,

307
00:18:38,063 --> 00:18:39,479
or if it's going to end.

308
00:18:41,188 --> 00:18:42,188
No.

309
00:18:43,854 --> 00:18:44,854
Well, I...

310
00:18:45,729 --> 00:18:46,729
I, uh...

311
00:18:48,479 --> 00:18:50,313
I appreciate your words.

312
00:19:06,771 --> 00:19:08,979
Mayor Fisk, I am so sorry,

313
00:19:09,063 --> 00:19:10,896
-I was--
-You don't have to apologize.

314
00:19:11,938 --> 00:19:13,479
It's curious, isn't it?

315
00:19:13,813 --> 00:19:15,521
When we act on impulse...

316
00:19:18,146 --> 00:19:20,188
we surprise even ourselves.

317
00:19:20,271 --> 00:19:21,813
I'd like to think I have

318
00:19:22,396 --> 00:19:23,854
more self-control than that.

319
00:19:23,938 --> 00:19:25,146
But you didn't.

320
00:19:27,146 --> 00:19:29,979
No. [chuckles softly]

321
00:19:35,104 --> 00:19:37,938
-[♪ suspenseful music playing]
-[sirens wailing]

322
00:19:43,521 --> 00:19:46,688
-[camera shutters clicking]
-[crowd clamoring indistinctly]

323
00:19:55,979 --> 00:19:58,521
[clamoring continues]

324
00:20:20,938 --> 00:20:22,604
-[BB] Can I get my shit back?
-No.

325
00:20:24,229 --> 00:20:26,146
This is kidnapping, you know.

326
00:20:27,813 --> 00:20:29,771
Okay, look, I understand that you're mad,

327
00:20:29,854 --> 00:20:31,479
-but--
-No, I'm not mad.

328
00:20:31,563 --> 00:20:32,771
I'm more than mad.

329
00:20:32,854 --> 00:20:34,479
Mad doesn't even begin to cover it.

330
00:20:35,896 --> 00:20:38,021
I can't keep stalling Buck.

331
00:20:38,104 --> 00:20:39,354
Dude, fuck him!

332
00:20:39,438 --> 00:20:40,729
Fuck him? Fuck you!

333
00:20:41,313 --> 00:20:43,688
Look, I get it, you used me, I used you.

334
00:20:43,771 --> 00:20:46,604
But I'm sorry, I thought
we actually had each other's backs.

335
00:20:47,646 --> 00:20:49,396
Your City Without Fear bullshit?

336
00:20:49,896 --> 00:20:51,021
It fucked us.

337
00:20:51,104 --> 00:20:53,604
So, what, you were working
with Karen Page?

338
00:20:58,146 --> 00:20:59,146
Wow.

339
00:20:59,604 --> 00:21:01,396
-How could you?
-How could I?

340
00:21:01,479 --> 00:21:04,063
I started The BB Report in my dorm room.

341
00:21:04,146 --> 00:21:07,271
I put every dime
and every hour of my life into it.

342
00:21:07,646 --> 00:21:10,229
Okay, people trusted it. It was real.

343
00:21:10,604 --> 00:21:14,646
And you turned it into some plastic
commercial for Fisk's fascist New York.

344
00:21:14,729 --> 00:21:17,354
-I didn't see you complaining.
-Okay. Well, clearly,

345
00:21:17,438 --> 00:21:20,729
you didn't see City Without Fear.
That's complaining.

346
00:21:21,479 --> 00:21:23,771
And all for what?
So that you can get outta Staten

347
00:21:23,854 --> 00:21:25,938
-and get a douchebag condo?
-Stop!

348
00:21:27,229 --> 00:21:28,479
He killed my uncle.

349
00:21:28,563 --> 00:21:29,854
-You don't know that.
-Yes,

350
00:21:30,479 --> 00:21:32,438
I do. And you do, too.

351
00:21:33,146 --> 00:21:35,813
You've just decided to turn a blind eye,
and that is your problem.

352
00:21:35,896 --> 00:21:36,979
Fine.

353
00:21:37,063 --> 00:21:38,646
Whatever. I did.

354
00:21:39,021 --> 00:21:41,229
It is, but you don't understand.

355
00:21:41,313 --> 00:21:42,813
That doesn't matter anymore.

356
00:21:43,271 --> 00:21:47,729
Because right now, Buck Cashman
is waiting for me to hand you over to him.

357
00:21:48,854 --> 00:21:50,063
And if I don't,

358
00:21:50,688 --> 00:21:51,896
then he comes after me.

359
00:21:53,021 --> 00:21:54,104
And then you,

360
00:21:54,604 --> 00:21:55,604
and my mom,

361
00:21:56,271 --> 00:21:57,771
and anyone I care about.

362
00:21:58,146 --> 00:22:01,229
So, BB, you should be fucking terrified
right now, 'cause I am.

363
00:22:01,896 --> 00:22:02,896
Then...

364
00:22:03,479 --> 00:22:05,146
we should probably get out of here.

365
00:22:06,104 --> 00:22:07,479
Yeah, we probably should.

366
00:22:10,354 --> 00:22:12,021
-Give me my phone.
-No.

367
00:22:12,104 --> 00:22:14,438
-Why?
-Because I don't trust you.

368
00:22:15,646 --> 00:22:17,313
Just give me a second to fucking think.

369
00:22:17,396 --> 00:22:19,271
Just sit there and let me think.

370
00:22:19,771 --> 00:22:21,813
[scoffs] Okay.

371
00:22:25,646 --> 00:22:26,646
We need a safe house.

372
00:22:26,729 --> 00:22:28,438
What are you, Jason Bourne?

373
00:22:28,521 --> 00:22:29,604
No, just...

374
00:22:31,063 --> 00:22:33,438
Some place Buck doesn't know about.

375
00:22:37,146 --> 00:22:39,146
I have a friend. A finance buddy.

376
00:22:39,229 --> 00:22:41,188
Works mostly in Hong Kong. I'll text him.

377
00:22:41,646 --> 00:22:42,813
Great.

378
00:22:44,771 --> 00:22:45,771
[sighs]

379
00:22:49,479 --> 00:22:50,688
[vibrates]

380
00:22:50,771 --> 00:22:53,229
[reporter] ...Assistant District Attorney
Kirsten McDuffie...

381
00:22:53,313 --> 00:22:55,813
Daniel is proving to be
quite a team player.

382
00:22:56,396 --> 00:22:57,396
Yes, he is.

383
00:22:57,813 --> 00:23:00,313
It's not easy to make the hard decisions.

384
00:23:01,771 --> 00:23:03,729
You think Karen Page knows?

385
00:23:04,063 --> 00:23:05,229
[Buck] Knows what, sir?

386
00:23:05,688 --> 00:23:07,813
That she is the wounded soldier

387
00:23:08,313 --> 00:23:10,188
screaming in the field,

388
00:23:10,604 --> 00:23:13,521
drawing her comrades
into the line of fire.

389
00:23:17,396 --> 00:23:19,854
-[people chattering indistinctly]
-[woman] Really?

390
00:23:20,229 --> 00:23:21,688
-That's good.
-Either way...

391
00:23:36,063 --> 00:23:37,521
[court officer] All rise.

392
00:23:45,354 --> 00:23:47,146
[Chief Justice Waters]
District Attorney Hochberg,

393
00:23:47,229 --> 00:23:48,771
your opening statement.

394
00:23:51,979 --> 00:23:52,979
Your Honors...

395
00:23:56,146 --> 00:23:59,396
I stand before you today
to ask that you convict

396
00:24:00,646 --> 00:24:02,313
and that you punish this woman,

397
00:24:03,104 --> 00:24:05,604
this criminal, Karen Page,

398
00:24:06,354 --> 00:24:09,271
for the crime she has committed
against our great city.

399
00:24:09,354 --> 00:24:11,896
Your Honors, I could argue
my client's innocence.

400
00:24:12,646 --> 00:24:15,771
I could argue
the illegitimacy of this court.

401
00:24:16,729 --> 00:24:18,604
I could argue against

402
00:24:19,021 --> 00:24:20,354
the Safer Streets Act.

403
00:24:20,438 --> 00:24:24,438
But first, I want you to think on
one very important concept.

404
00:24:26,021 --> 00:24:27,438
What is a vigilante?

405
00:24:28,354 --> 00:24:31,104
Is it he or she who breaks the law

406
00:24:31,188 --> 00:24:35,146
in order to get
their own version of justice? Or...

407
00:24:35,521 --> 00:24:37,604
is a vigilante the last resort

408
00:24:37,688 --> 00:24:39,188
to obtain the justice

409
00:24:39,271 --> 00:24:41,938
that a broken society
can no longer supply?

410
00:24:42,021 --> 00:24:44,354
The evidence will show that

411
00:24:45,063 --> 00:24:47,021
Miss Page is not a hero.

412
00:24:48,021 --> 00:24:49,604
She's not a "freedom fighter"

413
00:24:49,688 --> 00:24:51,729
for a noble resistance. No.

414
00:24:51,813 --> 00:24:52,813
No, she's...

415
00:24:53,313 --> 00:24:54,396
a criminal

416
00:24:55,188 --> 00:24:58,646
responsible for the destruction
of innocent human lives.

417
00:24:59,188 --> 00:25:02,313
[Kirsten] Your Honors,
you have a duty to this city,

418
00:25:02,396 --> 00:25:05,479
and you have a duty
to the ideals of this court,

419
00:25:07,146 --> 00:25:11,271
and fulfilling that duty
can only come to one conclusion.

420
00:25:11,354 --> 00:25:12,354
Guilty.

421
00:25:12,438 --> 00:25:13,604
Not guilty.

422
00:25:15,854 --> 00:25:16,854
Thank you.

423
00:25:17,688 --> 00:25:19,729
Prosecution can now call
its first witness.

424
00:25:19,813 --> 00:25:21,771
Your Honors, before we proceed...

425
00:25:22,646 --> 00:25:24,354
I'd like to bring in my co-counsel.

426
00:25:24,438 --> 00:25:26,271
[Hochberg] What-- Co-counsel?

427
00:25:26,354 --> 00:25:28,396
What, already calling for backup?

428
00:25:32,146 --> 00:25:33,813
[audience gasps]

429
00:25:34,229 --> 00:25:36,271
Matthew Murdock
for the defense, Your Honors.

430
00:25:37,063 --> 00:25:38,896
-[woman 1] Oh, my God!
-[man] Is that Matt Murdock?

431
00:25:38,979 --> 00:25:41,229
-[woman 2] Matt Murdock?
-[woman 3] My God. It's Matt Murdock?

432
00:25:41,313 --> 00:25:42,854
[Chief Justice Waters] Order in the court.

433
00:25:42,938 --> 00:25:44,646
[reporter] In a shocking turn of events,

434
00:25:44,729 --> 00:25:47,313
Matthew Murdock,
the missing lawyer from Hell's Kitchen,

435
00:25:47,396 --> 00:25:49,396
has just walked into the courtroom.

436
00:25:49,479 --> 00:25:51,979
Despite a citywide search,
Murdock has not been seen

437
00:25:52,063 --> 00:25:54,938
since the destruction of
his Brooklyn apartment months ago.

438
00:25:55,021 --> 00:25:58,229
Murdock is well known for
his heroic act of saving Mayor Fisk

439
00:25:58,313 --> 00:25:59,813
from vigilante gunfire.

440
00:25:59,896 --> 00:26:02,479
But he has now reappeared,
apparently, to support...

441
00:26:08,188 --> 00:26:09,313
[Matt] Officer Powell,

442
00:26:09,396 --> 00:26:13,104
tell me, what is the mission statement
for the Anti-Vigilante Task Force?

443
00:26:13,188 --> 00:26:16,729
To interdict, apprehend,
and prosecute extra-legal vigilantes

444
00:26:16,813 --> 00:26:18,479
to the fullest extent of the law.

445
00:26:18,563 --> 00:26:20,146
"To the fullest extent of the law"?

446
00:26:20,229 --> 00:26:21,729
That sounds serious.

447
00:26:22,313 --> 00:26:23,396
As a heart attack.

448
00:26:24,563 --> 00:26:25,771
[Matt] Huh.

449
00:26:25,854 --> 00:26:28,688
And, Officer Powell,
who formed the Task Force, and...

450
00:26:29,438 --> 00:26:31,896
created these, uh, parameters?

451
00:26:33,313 --> 00:26:34,313
Mayor Fisk.

452
00:26:36,313 --> 00:26:37,313
Of course.

453
00:26:37,396 --> 00:26:39,604
[Kirsten] Can you tell me about
those scars on your face?

454
00:26:40,104 --> 00:26:43,521
I got these in a firefight
with Daredevil and Frank Castle.

455
00:26:43,604 --> 00:26:45,813
-In Mr. Murdock's apartment?
-Yes.

456
00:26:47,604 --> 00:26:48,979
[Kirsten] Why were you there?

457
00:26:49,063 --> 00:26:52,854
Um, we were performing a welfare check.

458
00:26:54,313 --> 00:26:55,479
Welfare check?

459
00:26:57,479 --> 00:27:00,271
With assault rifles
and MRAP personnel carriers?

460
00:27:00,979 --> 00:27:03,729
I don't know, seems like
a lot of hardware for a blind lawyer.

461
00:27:03,813 --> 00:27:05,479
[audience chuckles]

462
00:27:08,104 --> 00:27:09,396
Was the defendant there?

463
00:27:12,396 --> 00:27:14,479
I was told she drove the getaway vehicle.

464
00:27:16,021 --> 00:27:17,438
You were told?

465
00:27:18,146 --> 00:27:20,271
What else did Officer Powell
tell you to do?

466
00:27:21,479 --> 00:27:23,188
Did he tell you to kill Hector Ayala?

467
00:27:23,854 --> 00:27:25,729
-Or maybe that was Mayor Fisk.
-Objection.

468
00:27:25,813 --> 00:27:28,104
Immaterial, misleading, and prejudicial.

469
00:27:28,188 --> 00:27:30,021
Sustained. Ms. McDuffie,

470
00:27:30,104 --> 00:27:32,188
I will caution you against these theatrics

471
00:27:32,271 --> 00:27:34,688
and remind you that
there's no jury to play to here.

472
00:27:34,771 --> 00:27:36,229
Sure about that, Your Honor?

473
00:27:39,771 --> 00:27:40,771
No further questions.

474
00:27:40,854 --> 00:27:41,854
Thank you.

475
00:27:49,938 --> 00:27:52,646
-[line rings]
-[woman on phone] Alan Steverud's office.

476
00:27:52,729 --> 00:27:53,771
It's me.

477
00:27:54,021 --> 00:27:55,313
I need the Attorney General.

478
00:27:56,646 --> 00:27:58,021
-[AG Steverud] Steverud.
-Alan,

479
00:27:58,396 --> 00:28:01,188
I think it's time we move forward
on the suspension paperwork.

480
00:28:01,688 --> 00:28:04,771
Fisk's reign is over.
But we do need to move quick, though.

481
00:28:06,104 --> 00:28:08,271
No, it's-- It's gotten outta hand. It's...

482
00:28:09,313 --> 00:28:11,146
Yeah-- Our window is now.

483
00:28:13,063 --> 00:28:14,063
Okay.

484
00:28:35,063 --> 00:28:36,063
Daniel?

485
00:28:37,313 --> 00:28:38,313
What's going on?

486
00:28:40,396 --> 00:28:41,396
Daniel!

487
00:28:43,229 --> 00:28:45,729
You know, it's not just Fisk and Buck.

488
00:28:46,563 --> 00:28:47,563
It's me, too.

489
00:28:48,479 --> 00:28:49,604
I've done things.

490
00:28:50,146 --> 00:28:52,521
Really, really fucked up things.

491
00:28:54,021 --> 00:28:55,396
What're you talking about?

492
00:28:57,646 --> 00:28:59,188
I went upstate with Buck,

493
00:29:00,521 --> 00:29:02,604
to the Catskills, and we buried a body.

494
00:29:04,229 --> 00:29:05,229
Jesus.

495
00:29:09,229 --> 00:29:11,188
And I wish I didn't know I did that.

496
00:29:16,896 --> 00:29:17,896
But I can't...

497
00:29:18,729 --> 00:29:20,854
have anyone else knowing I did that.

498
00:29:41,188 --> 00:29:42,188
Come on.

499
00:29:50,021 --> 00:29:51,604
This isn't a safe house, is it?

500
00:29:52,188 --> 00:29:53,688
Daniel. Daniel!

501
00:29:53,771 --> 00:29:55,146
Daniel, please! Daniel!

502
00:29:56,688 --> 00:30:00,521
Is this really the person you wanna be?
[breathing heavily]

503
00:30:10,021 --> 00:30:11,229
Fuck! Fuck.

504
00:30:11,313 --> 00:30:13,646
Come on. Come on, before he sees.

505
00:30:17,646 --> 00:30:19,104
Here, take this

506
00:30:19,604 --> 00:30:22,271
and go. Don't go home.
Don't tell me where.

507
00:30:22,354 --> 00:30:24,438
And do not go anyplace
he would look, okay?

508
00:30:25,188 --> 00:30:27,896
-What're you gonna do?
-Doing the right thing. Just let me.

509
00:30:30,938 --> 00:30:31,938
Thank you.

510
00:30:32,938 --> 00:30:34,104
Of course.

511
00:30:36,563 --> 00:30:37,729
Just make it count.

512
00:30:48,146 --> 00:30:50,688
[Chief Justice Waters] This court
is adjourned until tomorrow morning.

513
00:30:54,646 --> 00:30:55,896
-Yeah.
-Thank you.

514
00:30:57,604 --> 00:30:59,354
I've got it. You focus on the rest.

515
00:31:00,771 --> 00:31:03,396
-That went as well as I thought.
-Yeah, I know. It's okay.

516
00:31:03,479 --> 00:31:04,479
It's okay.

517
00:31:05,229 --> 00:31:06,229
Be careful.

518
00:31:06,313 --> 00:31:07,313
[Matt] You, too.

519
00:31:12,813 --> 00:31:14,188
They're not leaving, are they?

520
00:31:16,146 --> 00:31:17,313
No, they're not.

521
00:31:18,521 --> 00:31:20,021
[Cole] Cameras are all off, sir.

522
